text: Kurt Russel's character was literally shoveling fish guts to make ends meet in the OG, and was too ashamed to say anything.  Doubt the new ' Faris' character will be doing anything of the sort in this remake.  In addition, did we really need a gender reversal with this particular film to illustrate the empowerment of women?  Goldie was the brains behind the whole mini golf plan, spoke multiple languages, extremely wealthy and SHE ultimately made the decision to follow her heart.  MGM is, of course, free to green light and finance any prospective script it believes will make money - it is a free country after all.  However, it looks to be just another current hot-button issue movie executives (mainly white men) feel they can make a buck on - with complete disregard for taking on the true issues that plague the billion(s) dollar Hollywood industry - and they are 'banking' on it.  For me, I'm banking on the intelligent women in this country seeing it for the unashamed money grab it is.  As always, my 2 cents (and probably worth less than that)  :)
